    <item>
      <title>Re: Newbie Good Samaritans (AKA Ky's Chatter Box - 11/2/2004)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=133369#M133369</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I would guess my main, a half elf druid, was around level 10 or 11 when hunting in Everfrost one day. A player called out that he had a Staff of the Observers (a really uber weapon in those early days of '99!) to give to the first person who found him. Most will know that Everfrost is a large and often confusing zone with some highly dangerous places for a level 10 character, so it wasn't going to be a doddle - especially as there would doubtless have been at least 30 people in the zone in those days, so the competition would have been fierce.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I made an /ooc enquiry as to what the staff was, so as to establish whether I wanted to try for it or not, knowing nothing about it at the time. As a result, I got a tell from another stranger who said he was a ranger and could track the guy for me if I was interested in the staff, as it wouldn't be any use to him. I thanked him, we met up (probably by Bandl) and off we went. Sure enough the ranger found him, and I got the staff.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;That weapon was awesome in it's day, and my druid equipped it well into his 30's, continuing against all the perceived wisdom to melee at least part of every fight as indeed he still does once the mob has turned as a result of being snared. Of course, he has a better weapon these days, but I'll never forget that Staff of the Observers and the two kind strangers who combined their kind deeds to enable me to receive it.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Prior to that, and on my first day in EQ I received a different kind of "charitable act" altogether. I had dabbled in the beta, and was struggling to "get into" the game, not really finding anything to draw me in despite a long period of playing CRPGs etc. I was missing that certain something. I was messing around outside Qeynos when a rogue sent me a tell, asking if I wanted to make a fortune? Of course, I knew it was a scam, but I was level 1 and bored with nothing to lose so I went along with it to see where it would lead. He explained about a pot of gold or somesuch corny reward awaiting me in a hidden location only he knew about, and said I should follow him and he'd show me where it was. Now I must stress I knew this was not for real, but for the first time in the game I was intrigued.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The rogue led me into the secret world of the Rogues Guild in Qeynos, through a false wall in the tavern, and down some corridors. "You go on from here alone and I'll meet up with you" he told me, and off I went - straight through a trap in the floor to a water-filled pit in which I died instantly to a phirana or somesuch. Duly resurrected outside Qeynos I got a tell from the rogue apologising and offering to bring my corpse out if I would consent to him dragging it - which in those early days included the ability to loot the corpse!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Needless to say I never saw my corpse, and I chuckle to this day at how little he made off it, and wonder how many other "suckers" he caught out. But, and here is the point of the story, when I feigned mock indignation at being ripped off (knowing all along that I would be), his reply was a classic, and I knew there and then that EQ was the game for me, the ultimate role-playing experience with other real people.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;He simply said "I'm a rogue, what did you expect?"&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Not a very charitable act, not a good samaritan, but he did do me the favour of drawing me into the game, and I've played it ever since - although the rogue is about the only class I haven't tried!&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sun, 07 Nov 2004 11:00:25 GMT</pubDate>
