    <item>
      <title>Re: Newbie Good Samaritans (AKA Ky's Chatter Box - 11/2/2004)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=132949#M132949</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;As a young enchanter, I received many unexpected gifts.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The two most memorable gifts my enchanter received, were from a total strangers.&amp;nbsp; The first one was a Robe of the Oracle.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I was at the bank in Freeport, getting ready to log off for the evening.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Before camping,&amp;nbsp;a very nice&amp;nbsp;druid approached me and&amp;nbsp;asked it I would help him trade some items with his wizard.&amp;nbsp; This was long before the shared bank came into existence.&amp;nbsp; I told him I would, but how&amp;nbsp;could he be sure I was trustworthy?&amp;nbsp; He replied that&amp;nbsp;my guild had a long history of being honorable.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So I helped him and after we were done, I scurried out the door.&amp;nbsp; I then received a tell from the guy asking me to come back.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;When I returned,&amp;nbsp;the trade window popped up and inside was a robe.&amp;nbsp; I asked if he needed to trade this&amp;nbsp;item also and he replied, no --&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;it was mine to keep.&amp;nbsp; I politely declined the offer, saying I&amp;nbsp;helped him out of the generosity of my heart and didn't expect anything in return.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; He&amp;nbsp;chuckled and said that he no longer needed it -- it was just taking up room in the bank and&amp;nbsp;it was his way of saying, thank you.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I must admit, it was quite a&amp;nbsp;thrill receiving something so grand.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;It was a&amp;nbsp;massive improvement over the&amp;nbsp;gossamer robe I was wearing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The second most memorable gift, was while I was&amp;nbsp;visiting Queynos.&amp;nbsp; I was standing by the front gate, casting breeze and other buffs&amp;nbsp;on&amp;nbsp;all the low levels as they passed by.&amp;nbsp; It was a great way to practice my spells.&amp;nbsp; After awhile, a Ranger approached me and the trade window popped up with 2500p.&amp;nbsp; I quickly closed the window and told him he must have clicked on the wrong person.&amp;nbsp; He told me no, he had clicked on the&amp;nbsp;right person and&amp;nbsp;it was his way of thanking me for&amp;nbsp;keeping his alt buffed, which had helped a great deal.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;At level 16, I had only managed to save 300p.&amp;nbsp; Buying all those enchanter spells and trying to get my jewelry skills up, had kept me broke.&amp;nbsp; With 2500p, I was rich and didn't have to worry anymore about where my next cp was coming from.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
