      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I'm pretty much a newbie, as I only began playing the game in late May of this year. While my monk is now a proud 52, back when I was about level 4 or so, I had my first great good samaritan experience. I was hunting in the newbie area outside Freeport when I received a tell from an Iksar monk. I had never seen any Iksie yet and I hardly believed he was a monk. He asked me a few questions and then handed me two gems. I had never seen anything like those! He told me to sell them for some armor upgrades. I started to run off towards Boomba the Big but the Iksar stopped me and told me I would get a better deal at the female merchant farther in. I had no idea that Boomba gave lousy deals, but I also had no idea where she was! I followed the Iksie to her (near the entrance to North Freeport) and watched him feign death as a bunch of guards swarmed him. I had heard about this "feign death" and knew I had much to look forward to, but that was great to actually see it in action! The gems netted me about 100pp, a fortune it seemed! I don't know his name but I will always remember that time. &lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
