    <item>
      <title>Re: Newbie Good Samaritans</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=132505#M132505</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;This was posted a month or so ago, but it was such an awesome experience for me that I don't mind posting it again.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I&amp;nbsp;had a level 15 barbarian shaman I had been working on for over&amp;nbsp;2 weeks.&amp;nbsp; The spells were starting to get expensive for this constantly poor character so I had been farming spider silk, bone chips and bat wings to sell in the bazaar.&amp;nbsp; I had also been casting SoW, and other low level shaman spells for "donations only if you can afford it" in the Plane of Knowledge.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;One Saturday night I was having trouble sleeping so I got up and thought I would run into the PoK and:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1.&amp;nbsp; Practice summoning food and drink (working on conjuration skill)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2.&amp;nbsp; Practice "True North" (working on divination skill)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3.&amp;nbsp; Cast SoW and other low level spells on others for possible donations (but absolutely not required!)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I sent out an /ooc to let everyone in PoK know that I had set up shop at the big bank and proceeded to cast my practice spells until someone came around looking for some "fleety feeties..."&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I had been there for about 15 minutes and&amp;nbsp;had probably cast SoW a dozen times on various toons.&amp;nbsp; Things were slow.&amp;nbsp; I had noticed this one character fleeting around near where I was standing.&amp;nbsp; He had been there for about 5 or 10 minutes.&amp;nbsp; He suddenly came up to me and opened a trade window.&amp;nbsp; In it was 1,000 platinum and he had already clicked on the "trade" button!&amp;nbsp; I was shocked!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I immediately clicked on the cancel trade button, fearing that he had made a very serious mistake, but he immediately opened the trade window again.&amp;nbsp; Same amount!!!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I accepted the trade and then asked him why he was doing this.&amp;nbsp; It was such a shock to me.&amp;nbsp; I figured "no harm, no foul."&amp;nbsp; I could simply give it back to him when he realize the error.&amp;nbsp; But he came back and said, "I have well over 60,000 plat.&amp;nbsp; I simply do this on occasion because I can, friend."&amp;nbsp; Well, I couldn't believe my good fortune!&amp;nbsp; I immediately /kneel in his presence and thanked him.&amp;nbsp; I asked if there was ANYTHING I, as a wimpy little level 15 shaman, could do to thank him.&amp;nbsp; His response, "Do the same thing some day when you are in the same position, friend."&amp;nbsp; Doing a quick /who, I found that he was a "Level 69 character!!!"&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Flush with 1,000 platinum, I went off to the bazaar to see if there was anything I could purchase that would improve my "shammy" but didn't find anything of interest.&amp;nbsp; I guess I was just&amp;nbsp;getting sleepy again.&amp;nbsp; So, I started to leave the bazaar and go back to PoK when suddenly a trade window opened again.&amp;nbsp; Another 1,000 platinum!&amp;nbsp; All I had to do was click on the trade button.&amp;nbsp; Well I did it and found it was the SAME character that had given me the plat over in PoK not, 30 minutes earlier.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Again, he reminded me that this was his way of helping the game and others.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This made such an impression on me that I went back to PoK began casting&amp;nbsp;SoW and every other minor spell I had on anyone that hailed me.&amp;nbsp; I forced those that wanted to donate to keep their donations and told them, that someone else had donated for them and that as long as I could keep my mana up I was casting until no one else wanted SoW.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I managed to cast for at least an hour with brief "sits" in between to bring my mana back up.&amp;nbsp; That was a complete blast!!!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I do not plan on giving out the name of my benefactor as I don't want him to be overwhemed by beggers, etc.&amp;nbsp; But I&amp;nbsp;have him in my friends list and I check every time I jump on to see if he is online.&amp;nbsp; I can hardly wait to be one of the first to "/salute" when he dings level 70!!!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I will remember this for as long as I play&amp;nbsp;Everquest.&amp;nbsp; One day, I hope to be able to identify a lowly character, practicing his skills and working to increase his plat, just like he did.&amp;nbsp; I will give me the chance to continue the legacy he started with me!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I hope this brought a smile to your face!&amp;nbsp; Generousity like this is uncommon, and I hope to do the same thing one day!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;/KNEEL....&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;/BOW.....&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;/SALUTE&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As a post script to this story, three nights after this message was originally posted in TNZ, I logged on to EQ and did a quick who on my friends list and found that my benefactor had in fact made level 70 in the few days since this event occured.&amp;nbsp; I was able to be one of the first to send him a /tell congratulating him on his accomplishment.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;BTW, he is still in my friends list and I see him on all the time.&amp;nbsp; Since I don't want to be a pest, I don't say hi much but it is comforting to me to&amp;nbsp;know that he's always there, protecting the less powerful in Norrath!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
