      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;This was when my bard was in the mid-40s... not sure if that qualifies as "newbie", but I'm going to tell it anyway.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I was scrounging for cheap&amp;nbsp;gear upgrades in the bazaar, and&amp;nbsp;just about to leave, when a higher level bard&amp;nbsp;by the name of Jukebox walked up and inspected, then&amp;nbsp;hailed me. I returned his greeting, and he began asking me&amp;nbsp;questions about my character, how long I had been playing, what I wanted to accomplish, etc. I was a little confused at first, but I answered each one, and next thing I knew, the trade window opened up with a Thunderous Drum of Karana, and he had already confirmed the trade.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I paused for a long time, in disbelief that someone was just giving me such an amazing drum. They sold for about 10k at the time, which was about 10x as much money as I had ever seen at once. He told me to go ahead and take it, and I finally clicked trade. He told me to equip it, and let him know how I liked it (I loved it!). I thanked him many times... hopefully not enough to make a pest of myself.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;That was probably the one&amp;nbsp;main thing that motivated me to stick with my bard, and&amp;nbsp;get him to where he is now. Unfortunately, I think the bard who gave me that drum left the game, because I haven't seen him around for a long time. If I do, I will definitely have to thank him again :smileywink:&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
